{"id":"7762","name":"AntiPaywall","tagline":"Quick and easy access to various sites with Paywalls.","icon":"ios14 c946986751 g59760","latest":"23997","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"Banner\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/9xoDELz.png\"></p>\n<h2>AntiPaywall</h2>\n<p>AntiPaywall is a Shortcut that will let you access many paywalled websites, through three different methods:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can open the site with Outline.com</li>\n<li>You can open the site in preview mode within the Shortcuts app, with option to download to Files App. Keep in mind that it is possible that the site won’t appear exactly like if you were accessing it through a browser. (Credits to @robric18 for letting me use his method in my shortcut)</li>\n<li>You can download the article to the Apple Notes app</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can either have the URL you want to access stored in your clipboard, or you use the share sheet to use the shortcut.</p>\n<h4>Customizing the shortcut</h4>\n<p><em>Scroll trough the actions to find the comments indicating where to modify the shortcut.</em> You can change the Notes Folder where the articles will be saved. You can also add a file path when saving the article as a webpage so you don’t need to manually select the Folder every time you download one.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/epmFY0o.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"iPad\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/5kjHO0g.jpg\"></p>\n<h3>List of sites in which the Shortcut has been tested</h3>\n<p><strong>Medium</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Outline ✅</li>\n<li>Preview ✅</li>\n<li>Notes ⚠️ To download to Notes you should first open with Outline, and then run the shortcut again to save it as a Note.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The New Yorker</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Outline ✅</li>\n<li>Preview ✅</li>\n<li>Notes ⚠️ To download to Notes you should first open with Outline, and then run the shortcut again to save it as a Note.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The New York Times</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Outline ❌</li>\n<li>Preview ✅</l